1. Swedish Kelly-list
---------------------
Used for: the word list and the CEFR level (A1–C2) of each word.

The Swedish Kelly-list is a CEFR-graded list of high-frequency Swedish
vocabulary, created at the University of Gothenburg (Språkbanken) as part of
the KELLY project. It is openly licensed under a Creative Commons license.

The list is accessed in this project via the dataset published at:
  https://github.com/codesue/kelly

Reference:
  Volodina, E. & Kokkinakis, S. J. (2012). Introducing the Swedish Kelly-list,
  a new lexical e-resource for Swedish. LREC 2012.


2. Folkets lexikon (the People's Dictionary)
--------------------------------------------
Used for: the English translations and example sentences.

Folkets lexikon is a free Swedish–English dictionary hosted by KTH Royal
Institute of Technology. The dictionary data is released under the
Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 2.5 Generic license (CC BY-SA 2.5).
  https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.5/

Source:
  https://folkets-lexikon.csc.kth.se/folkets/


